race.comment: ELYSIUM (13) resumes here but showed enough in her first NSW preparation to warrant serious consideration in a race of this calibre. Looks the runner in this field with the most upside and should be right there at the business end. The well-related MONARCH EXPRESS (3) (half to G3 winner and G1 placed Mirette) got an overdue victory at the latest effort and will have taken some confidence from that win. Gets some weight off with the 2kg claim and should be going close again. MINTO'S PRINCE (2) will strip fitter second-up from the break and looks ready for the step-up in trip now. Sure to be competitive. HEY CHARDONNAY (14) doesn't win out of turn but is usually thereabouts and may earn some minor money. SUNDAY GEORGIE (11) next best.
